sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potential Raspberry Robin Registry Set Internet Settings ZoneMap
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects registry modifications related to the proxy configuration of the system, potentially associated with the Raspberry Robin malware, as seen in campaigns running in Q1 2024.
Raspberry Robin may alter proxy settings to circumvent security measures, ensuring unhindered connection with Command and Control servers for maintaining control over compromised systems if there are any proxy settings that are blocking connections.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Windows Powershell User-Agent Usage
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Windows Powershell User-Agent Usage"; flow:established,to_server; http.user_agent; content:"Mozilla/"; startswith; content:") WindowsPowerShell/"; distance:0; fast_pattern; classtype:not-suspicious; sid:2033355; rev:1; metadata:attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2021_07_16, deployment Perimeter, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2021_07_16;)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script uses VBScript to download and install an MSI file.  It first checks if a designated folder ("C:\home") exists; if not, it creates it.  A PowerShell command is constructed to download a file from "http://my-sharepoint-inc.com/cloudshare/atr/ca" to "C:\home\file.msi".  The download process is wrapped in a try-catch block, logging potential errors to "C:\home\error.log" and standard output to "C:\home\temp.log".  After the download, the script attempts to execute "msiexec.exe" with the downloaded MSI file in silent mode ("/qn") and with administrative privileges ("runas").  If the MSI file download fails, an error message is displayed. Finally, the script releases all object variables.
